title: feat: Add schematic_table element
description: Adds a new schematic_table element to the circuit-json specification, enabling structured data display in schematics.
body:
This pull request introduces a new schematic_table element to the circuit-json specification. This element allows for the        
creation of tables within schematics, which can be used for displaying structured data like bills of materials, pinouts, or other notes.      

The implementation includes:                                                                                                                  

 • A new schematic_table.ts file defining the SchematicTable interface and its corresponding Zod schema.                                      
 • The SchematicTableCell interface and schema for individual cells.                                                                          
 • Integration of the new element into any_circuit_element.                                                                                   
 • A basic test case to validate parsing of the schematic_table element. 

Sparkfun reference:

title: feat: implement schematic_table
description: This PR introduces support for rendering schematic_table and schematic_table_cell elements in the schematic SVG output.
body:
This PR introduces support for rendering schematic_table and schematic_table_cell elements in the schematic SVG output.

Key Features:

 • Table Rendering: Adds a new function, createSvgObjectsFromSchematicTable, to draw table borders, grid lines, and
   cell content.
 • Dynamic Sizing: Implements getTableDimensions to dynamically calculate column widths and row heights based on
   cell content and font sizes, ensuring tables are appropriately sized.
 • Merged Cells: The rendering logic now correctly handles merged cells by omitting internal grid lines.
 • Bounds Calculation: Updates getSchematicBoundsFromCircuitJson to accurately calculate the bounding box for
   schematic_table elements, ensuring they are fully contained within the SVG.
 • Customization: Supports custom border widths and text alignments.

Testing:

 • Adds a new test file, tests/sch/schematic-table.test.tsx, with multiple test cases to cover various
   configurations, including:
    • Default rendering
    • Different font sizes
    • Text alignments
    • Custom border widths
    • Empty and merged cells
    • Specified dimensions vs. dynamic sizing

title: Improved handling of the `ViaPossibilitiesSolver` part of the `MultiHeadSolver`
description: Fixes autorouting failure when the ViaPossibilitiesSolver2 fails to find a solution within the iteration limit, preventing the MultiHeadSolver from failing directly after a single iteration.
body: ### Why are we changing this? We've observed that the MultiHeadSolver failed after a single iteration. This was caused by the `ViaPossibilitiesSolver2` not finding a solution within the iteration limit. This pull request introduces a couple of fixes for the same problem. ### What has changed? - The entire MultiHeadSolver no longer fails directly when a single iteration of the `ViaPossibilitiesSolver2` doesn't find a solution - The `ViaPossibilitiesSolver2` could not find a solution because it iteratively added a via just slightly closer to the target. By adding a floating point tolerance this is no longer the case - Limit the search to a maximum number of vias for a single trace within a node Fixes https://github.com/tscircuit/tscircuit-autorouter/issues/191 ### Visualisation [Highdensity fixture 79](https://capacity-node-autorouter-git-via-possibilities-tscircuit.vercel.app/?fixtureId=%7B%22path%22%3A%22examples%2Fhighdensity%2Fhighdensity79.fixture.tsx%22%7D) can now be solved while this was not previously the case
